{"title":"Bontrager’s GR Elite alloy gravel bar hopes to tame hand fatigue with buillt-in Iso Zone.","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/23/bontrager-elite-gr-gravel-bars-weight-sizing-availability-dropbars-offroad-allroad/","date":1627058245000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Not all drop bars excel in every riding style — most would have a different setup for a crit race and a gravel ride. Bontrager feels the same but takes a less exaggerated approach than most to the subject.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view-.jpeg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x363/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" alt=\"Bontrager Gravel Elite Handlebar. 3:4 view\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view-.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--297x223.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--120x90.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--560x420.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--80x60.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--265x198.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 265w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view-.jpeg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x363/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" ezoid=\"0.4696578280524073\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view-.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--297x223.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--120x90.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--560x420.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--80x60.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115138/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-34-view--265x198.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 265w\"></a></p><h2>What is it — Bontrager GR Elite Gravel Bar</h2><p>Bontrager’s new GR Elite gravel bar (GR standing for gravel no doubt) includes all the major features of a successful gravel bar; short reach, flared but not insane, additional padding that doesn’t look like campfire marshmallows, and it keeps shifters in a semi-neutral position.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail-.jpeg\" alt=\"Bontrager Gravel Elite Handlebar. flare detail\" width=\"640\" height=\"404\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail--297x187.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail--120x76.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail--297x187.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115125/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-flare-detail--120x76.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>The GR Elite features Bontrager’s new Adventure Fit geometry that provides easy access to controls from any hand position. The GR Elite is the most flared bar from Bontrager to date, offering a 13-degree flare a 128mm drop, and a 75mm reach —&nbsp; aiming to keep the bar nimble in the challenging sectors and comfortable on the long hauls.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail-.jpeg\" alt=\"Bontrager Gravel Elite Handlebar. reach and drop detail\" width=\"640\" height=\"404\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail--297x187.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail--120x76.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail--297x187.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115105/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-reach-and-drop-detail--120x76.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>Lately, the new spin on gravel bars seems to be keeping the hand positions as close to neutral as possible while giving the rider enough flare to feel comfortable. The Bontrager GR Elite looks to split the difference allowing for the rider to keep a reasonably neutral setup while taking advantage of the flare for comfort and lower back ease.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail-.jpeg\" alt=\"Bontrager Gravel Elite Handlebar. IsoZone padding detail\" width=\"640\" height=\"331\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail--297x154.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail--120x62.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail--297x154.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115113/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-IsoZone-padding-detail--120x62.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>Bontrager’s new GR Elite bars feature replaceable <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2016/12/06/review-comfy-bontrager-rxl-padded-handlebar-w-prologo-onetouch-2-cpc-foam-bar-tape/\">IsoZone EVA pads</a> for those looking for another layer of comfort to help reduce road and gravel vibrations. Though alloy bars do not offer all the vibration qualities of carbon, the cost, weight, and stiffness are enough to roll the dice for this as your next gravel bar.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing-.jpeg\" alt=\"Bontrager Gravel Elite Handlebar. Di2 routing\" width=\"640\" height=\"333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing--297x155.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing--120x62.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing--297x155.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115109/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar.-Di2-routing--120x62.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>If you’re running <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/03/long-term-review-shimano-grx-di2-gravel-1x11-groupset/\">Shimano GRX or any Di2 components</a>, you’ll be stoked to know Bontrager’s GR Elite bars have fully integrated internal wire routing and are primed for Shimano Junction-A (bar end style) routing.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo-.jpeg\" alt=\"Bontrager Gravel Elite Handlebar logo\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--560x420.jpeg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--80x60.jpeg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--265x198.jpeg 265w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--297x223.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--120x90.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--560x420.jpeg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--80x60.jpeg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115130/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-logo--265x198.jpeg 265w\"></a></p><ul><li>13-degree flare allows for more control in the drops</li><li>Replaceable IsoZone EVA pads while maintaining the original grip diameter</li><li>Compatible with Shimano EW-RS910 bar end Junction-A for cleaner Di2 routing</li><li>Laser-etched brake lever position lines for spot-on control setup</li><li>Compatible with clip-on aero bars</li><li><strong>Price:</strong> $99</li><li><strong>Available Sizes:</strong> 38cm, 40cm, 42cm, and 44cm.</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs-.jpeg\" alt=\"Bontrager Gravel Elite Handlebar weight and sizing specs\" width=\"640\" height=\"263\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs--297x122.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs--120x49.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs--297x122.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/23115135/Bontrager-Gravel-Elite-Handlebar-weight-and-sizing-specs--120x49.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/equipment/cycling-components/bike-handlebars-accessories/bike-handlebars/road-bike-handlebars/bontrager-gr-elite-road-handlebar/p/34938/?colorCode=black\">The Bontrager GR Elites are available now from Trek dealers and Bontrager’s global network of retail partners.&nbsp;</a></p></div></div>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7f5fb62e8d983a1b461b301c02aabb5eeb4bb96e380292c14feda3cbe5f2855a","category":"Cycling"}